cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR 

The paper deals with analyzing facial expressions in videos, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of machine learning algorithms for recognizing emotions also suggests the paper could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions using feature difference contrast, which is a technique used in information retrieval (cs.IR), and the use of databases for testing the algorithms, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
